Class SyndicationExtensionAdapter

Represents a System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator and SyndicationResourceLoadSettings that are used to fill a IExtensibleSyndicationObject.

GetExtensions(Collection<Type>)

Creates a collection of ISyndicationExtension instances for the specified types.

Declaration
public static Collection<ISyndicationExtension> GetExtensions(Collection<Type> types)
Parameters
Type Name Description
System.Collections.ObjectModel.Collection<System.Type> types

A System.Collections.ObjectModel.Collection<T> collection of System.Type objects to be instantiated.
Returns
Type Description
System.Collections.ObjectModel.Collection<ISyndicationExtension>

A System.Collections.ObjectModel.Collection<T> collection of ISyndicationExtension objects instantiated using the supplied types.
Remarks

Each ISyndicationExtension instance in the System.Collections.ObjectModel.Collection<T> collection will be instantiated using its default constructor.

Types that are a null reference or do not implement the ISyndicationExtension interface are ignored.

GetExtensions(Collection<Type>, Dictionary<String, String>)

Creates a collection of ISyndicationExtension instances for the specified types.

Declaration
public static Collection<ISyndicationExtension> GetExtensions(Collection<Type> types, Dictionary<string, string> namespaces)
Parameters
Type Name Description
System.Collections.ObjectModel.Collection<System.Type> types

A System.Collections.ObjectModel.Collection<T> collection of System.Type objects that represent user-defined syndication extensions to be instantiated.
System.Collections.Generic.Dictionary<System.String, System.String> namespaces

A collection of XML nameapces that are used to filter the available native framework syndication extensions.
Returns
Type Description
System.Collections.ObjectModel.Collection<ISyndicationExtension>

A System.Collections.ObjectModel.Collection<T> collection of ISyndicationExtension objects instantiated using the supplied types and namespaces.
Remarks

This method instantiates all of the available native framework syndication extensions, and then filters them based on the XML namespaces and prefixes contained in the supplied namespaces. The user defined syndication extensions are then instantiated, and are added to the return collection if they do not already exist.

Exceptions
Type Condition
System.ArgumentNullException

The types is a null reference (Nothing in Visual Basic).
System.ArgumentNullException

The namespaces is a null reference (Nothing in Visual Basic).
